title: Noteworthy ETF Outflows: IWO, SAIC, MMS, TREX - Nasdaq.com
text: Looking today at week-over-week shares outstanding changes among the universe of ETFs covered at ETF Channel , one standout is the iShares Russell 2000 Growth ETF (Symbol: IWO) where we have detected an approximate $57.8 million dollar outflow -- that's a 0.7% decrease week over week (from 45,900,000 to 45,600,000). Among the largest underlying components of IWO, in trading today Science Applications International Corp (Symbol: SAIC) is up about 2.8%, MAXIMUS Inc. (Symbol: MMS) is up about 2.6%, and Trex Co Inc (Symbol: TREX) is up by about 1.9%.
